## Supporting class (new): BackpackAccessTracker

Add a simple weak map keyed by player UUID. Populate it from the places that currently open a `BackpackContainer` server-side (see callers of `sophisticatedCore_openMenu` with a `BackpackContext`). Clear it on `PlayerLoggedOutEvent` / `ServerPlayConnectionEvents.DISCONNECT`.

```java
// new file: sophisticatedbackpacks-.../backpack/BackpackAccessTracker.java
package net.p3pp3rf1y.sophisticatedbackpacks.backpack;

import net.minecraft.class_3222;
import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.HashSet;
import java.util.Map;
import java.util.Set;
import java.util.UUID;

public final class BackpackAccessTracker {
    private static final Map<UUID, Set<UUID>> ALLOWED = new HashMap<>();

    private BackpackAccessTracker() {}

    public static synchronized void grant(class_3222 player, UUID backpackUuid) {
        ALLOWED.computeIfAbsent(player.method_5667(), k -> new HashSet<>()).add(backpackUuid);
    }

    public static synchronized boolean canRead(class_3222 player, UUID backpackUuid) {
        Set<UUID> s = ALLOWED.get(player.method_5667());
        return s != null && s.contains(backpackUuid);
    }

    public static synchronized void clear(UUID playerId) {
        ALLOWED.remove(playerId);
    }
}
```

## Supporting change: flip getOrCreate → get

In `BackpackStorage`, add a non-creating `getBackpackContents(UUID)` sibling of `getOrCreateBackpackContents`. The existing `getOrCreate` should stay available for paths that legitimately need to create new entries (placing a new backpack, etc.).

## Defense-in-depth (optional)

Rate-limit the payload to e.g. 10/sec per player. Log any attempt to read a UUID that is not in the player's allow-list (useful for spotting clients running exploit kits).
